      <bioghist altrender="biography" encodinganalog="545" id="a2">
         <head>History</head>
         <p>The <title render="italic">Niagara Frontier Review</title> was a small magazine of poetry and prose published in <geogname>Buffalo, New York</geogname>, from <date>1964-1966</date>.  The editorial staff  included <persname>Charles Olson</persname>, <persname>Harvey Brown</persname>, <persname>Charles Boer</persname> and others.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520" id="a3">
         <head>Scope and Content</head>
         <p>The collection consists of correspondence and submissions addressed to <persname>Charles Boer</persname> from <persname>LeRoi Jones</persname>, <persname>Robert Creeley</persname> and <persname>Robert Kelly</persname>.  Also included are photocopies of   manuscripts by <persname>Charles Olson</persname>.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <relatedmaterial encodinganalog="544 1" id="a6">
         <head>Related Material</head>
         <p>Archives and Special Collections has a substantial collection of literary materials, especially pertaining to <extref href="http://doddcenter.uconn.edu/asc/findaids/Olson/MSS19690001.html"><persname>Charles Olson</persname></extref>, 
            his students, <corpname>Black Mountain College</corpname> and the Beat poets. See especially, the <extref href="http://doddcenter.uconn.edu/asc/findaids/Creeley/MSS19780008.html">Robert Creeley</extref> 
            Papers and the <extref href="http://doddcenter.uconn.edu/asc/findaids/Kelly/MSS20010081.htl">Robert Kelly</extref> Papers.  
            For detailed information on these collections please contact the <extref href="http://doddcenter.uconn.edu/asc/dodda2z/curatorinfo.cfm?curatorinfo=6">curator</extref> or ask at the reference desk.</p>
      </relatedmaterial>
